<TITLE> Police arrest alleged child rapist </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 19 (bdnews24.com)  The Uttarkhan Police arrested the main accused of a child rape case from Hemayatpur, Savar on Sunday. One Nayan, known as Lengra Nayan, was accused of raping a two year and nine month-old child. She was raped on Apr 6, when her mother Norzila Begum took the child to a house where she worked as a domestic aid. The mother found her child in a pool of blood in a room next door later that day. The victim was admitted to Dhaka Medical College Hospital at 12.30am the same day. Duty doctor Salahuddin Mollah had told bdnews24.com that the child was in a critical situation. Later she was shifted to the one stop crisis centre of the hospital. On Apr 7, grandfather of the child, Nazrul Islam, filed a case against threeShahin, Rubel and Lengra Nayan. Police arrested Shahin and Rubel just after the case was lodged, but Nayan had managed to elude the law enforcers till now. bdnew
